Female
. Protarsomere I slightly narrower than in males. Sternite VIII heart-shaped, posterior margin rounded with shallow emargination in middle, surface laterally with two elevated plates, long setae accumulated along posterior and inner margins of those plates, tignum short, 0.30 times as long as sternite VIII, slightly asymmetrical to left (
